1
00:00:51,480 --> 00:00:52,120
Take it back!

2
00:00:52,120 --> 00:00:52,680
What the hell?

3
00:00:52,680 --> 00:00:53,760
Just take your damn things back!

4
00:00:53,760 --> 00:00:55,280
What on earth is happening here?

5
00:00:55,280 --> 00:00:57,560
Have you ever had a friend
secretly sleep with your ex?

6
00:00:57,560 --> 00:00:58,960
Even if he's my ex...

7
00:00:58,960 --> 00:01:00,960
you still have no right
to mess with him!

8
00:01:08,240 --> 00:01:08,440
Huh?

9
00:01:08,640 --> 00:01:08,840
Hey!

10
00:01:08,960 --> 00:01:10,440
Hey!

11
00:01:10,640 --> 00:01:11,760
Oh, enough!

12
00:01:11,760 --> 00:01:12,840
Explain this to me.
Who is this?

13
00:01:12,840 --> 00:01:13,720
I don't know him.

14
00:01:13,720 --> 00:01:15,000
But I've seen this engineer before...

15
00:01:15,000 --> 00:01:16,200
acting all sketchy on the plane.

16
00:01:16,200 --> 00:01:17,200
Could he be an assassin?

17
00:01:18,880 --> 00:01:19,840
I knew it!

18
00:01:19,880 --> 00:01:21,880
You must be one of them.

19
00:01:22,240 --> 00:01:22,880
Sky!

20
00:01:22,880 --> 00:01:23,880
No need to mourn...

21
00:01:23,880 --> 00:01:25,920
because you'll be next.

22
00:01:45,000 --> 00:01:46,520
Hey!

23
00:01:46,520 --> 00:01:47,920
Wait...

24
00:01:47,920 --> 00:01:49,080
Oh, come on, Kree!

25
00:01:49,080 --> 00:01:51,320
Are you secretly sleeping
under the office counter?

26
00:01:51,320 --> 00:01:52,000
Man, you're on leave without pay...

27
00:01:52,000 --> 00:01:53,000
and still haven't found a job yet...

28
00:01:53,000 --> 00:01:53,560
so you're sleeping here

29
00:01:53,560 --> 00:01:54,960
to save on
water and electricity bills, right?

30
00:01:54,960 --> 00:01:57,440
Wow. You saw just this much
and you...

31
00:01:57,440 --> 00:01:58,600
already figured all that out?

32
00:01:58,600 --> 00:02:00,120
You brought pajamas...

33
00:02:00,120 --> 00:02:01,760
an eye mask...

34
00:02:01,760 --> 00:02:03,520
plus your hair is a total mess.

35
00:02:03,520 --> 00:02:05,800
If I couldn't figure it out,
it would ruin my reputation...

36
00:02:05,800 --> 00:02:07,720
You're that little detective, All-New.

37
00:02:07,720 --> 00:02:10,040
Hey, no way.
Why do I have to be little?

38
00:02:11,000 --> 00:02:12,640
And what's with all the stuff
you're carrying?

39
00:02:12,640 --> 00:02:14,320
You call this a lot? Huh?

40
00:02:14,320 --> 00:02:17,120
Then what is this box?

41
00:02:17,120 --> 00:02:18,840
Huh? It's not mine.

42
00:02:18,840 --> 00:02:20,200
I didn't see it here yesterday.

43
00:02:20,200 --> 00:02:21,560
Where did it come from?

44
00:02:21,560 --> 00:02:23,160
Could it be...

45
00:02:23,160 --> 00:02:24,400
All-New.

46
00:02:25,240 --> 00:02:29,200
I can sense a certain presence.

47
00:02:29,200 --> 00:02:31,120
You think someone
is hiding around here, right?

48
00:02:31,120 --> 00:02:32,600
Yeah.

49
00:02:32,600 --> 00:02:35,600
And I think it's really close, too.

50
00:02:39,440 --> 00:02:43,280
Good morning!

51
00:02:43,280 --> 00:02:44,720
Look-Kai, hello.

52
00:02:44,720 --> 00:02:46,240
You're at work so early.

53
00:02:46,240 --> 00:02:48,400
Your bag looks quite chic, Look-Kai.

54
00:02:49,360 --> 00:02:50,800
Oh, you noticed?

55
00:02:50,800 --> 00:02:52,640
I actually meant...

56
00:02:52,640 --> 00:02:54,280
this box right here.

57
00:02:54,280 --> 00:02:56,680
What?
That doesn't belong to me.

58
00:02:56,680 --> 00:02:58,960
Let me take a look at it.

59
00:02:58,960 --> 00:03:00,800
Oh, wait, wait! Hold on!

60
00:03:00,800 --> 00:03:02,800
I think I've seen this box
somewhere before.

61
00:03:10,320 --> 00:03:14,320
I think those assassins are back.

62
00:03:14,440 --> 00:03:16,360
What...what assassins?

63
00:03:16,360 --> 00:03:17,360
To be honest...

64
00:03:17,360 --> 00:03:19,840
we don't really know who they are.

65
00:03:19,840 --> 00:03:22,920
All we know is
they're a group of people who...

66
00:03:22,920 --> 00:03:24,760
will try anything to steal classified info.

67
00:03:24,760 --> 00:03:25,880
They sent Peck...

68
00:03:25,880 --> 00:03:27,480
to be a pilot at Glamorous Airline...

69
00:03:27,480 --> 00:03:30,120
and Pong, a cop.

70
00:03:30,120 --> 00:03:30,840
They will do absolutely anything,

71
00:03:30,840 --> 00:03:33,280
including taking lives.

72
00:03:46,600 --> 00:03:47,600
Hey!

73
00:03:49,960 --> 00:03:50,200
Huh?

74
00:03:50,200 --> 00:03:53,560
Hey!

75
00:03:53,560 --> 00:03:55,040
Oh, enough!

76
00:03:55,040 --> 00:03:56,080
Explain this to me.
Who is this?

77
00:03:56,080 --> 00:03:58,080
I don't know him.

78
00:03:58,080 --> 00:03:59,520
But I've seen this
technician before...

79
00:03:59,520 --> 00:04:01,000
acting all sketchy on the plane.

80
00:04:01,000 --> 00:04:02,080
What the hell are
you on about, Glasses?

81
00:04:02,080 --> 00:04:03,720
You scared the hell out of me.

82
00:04:03,720 --> 00:04:05,200
Could he be an assassin?

83
00:04:08,080 --> 00:04:09,920
Hey! Is this yours after all?

84
00:04:09,920 --> 00:04:11,480
You must be working
with the assassins!

85
00:04:11,480 --> 00:04:13,480
Kree, Look-Kai,
watch out!

86
00:04:16,280 --> 00:04:19,320
What do you mean assassin?
This is Mr. Prayoon.

87
00:04:20,040 --> 00:04:20,960
You know him, Look-Kai?

88
00:04:20,960 --> 00:04:22,440
Yes, I do.

89
00:04:22,440 --> 00:04:25,240
Actually, I'm the one
who invited him here.

90
00:04:25,240 --> 00:04:27,720
We're finally living in peace now.

91
00:04:27,720 --> 00:04:28,760
Let's hope it stays that way.

92
00:04:28,760 --> 00:04:31,120
Then shall we welcome Mr. Prayoon...

93
00:04:31,120 --> 00:04:34,320
to our AFS project?

94
00:04:34,320 --> 00:04:35,440
The AFS project?

95
00:04:35,440 --> 00:04:36,360
Does that still exist?

96
00:04:36,360 --> 00:04:39,640
Yes, it does.
"A Fixer Swap."

97
00:04:39,640 --> 00:04:40,960
Huh?

98
00:04:41,600 --> 00:04:44,920
Today,
Eight-Sided Mirror presents...

99
00:04:44,920 --> 00:04:46,280
A Fixer Swap!

100
00:04:46,280 --> 00:04:47,560
It's an exchange program...

101
00:04:47,560 --> 00:04:49,000
allowing technicians
from each department

102
00:04:49,000 --> 00:04:50,240
to learn from one another...

103
00:04:50,240 --> 00:04:52,520
so our airline can operate...

104
00:04:52,520 --> 00:04:53,800
systematically and efficiently.

105
00:04:53,800 --> 00:04:55,560
For what?

106
00:04:55,560 --> 00:04:57,000
Well, for entertainment purposes,
of course!

107
00:04:57,000 --> 00:04:58,440
No, I'm not entertained.

108
00:04:58,440 --> 00:04:59,960
I object!

109
00:04:59,960 --> 00:05:02,120
A rude person like him
is not fit for our department.

110
00:05:02,120 --> 00:05:02,880
What?

111
00:05:02,880 --> 00:05:03,920
Now, it’s all dirty!

112
00:05:03,920 --> 00:05:06,480
So what, you want me
to throw the whole thing out?

113
00:05:06,480 --> 00:05:07,720
Stop whining, Glasses.

114
00:05:07,720 --> 00:05:08,720
We'll completely lose
our first-class standards.

115
00:05:08,720 --> 00:05:09,920
I deeply apologize, sir.

116
00:05:09,920 --> 00:05:11,760
for causing a misunderstanding, sir.

117
00:05:11,760 --> 00:05:13,360
But it's quite alright, sir.

118
00:05:13,360 --> 00:05:16,080
I will definitely improve myself, sir.

119
00:05:16,080 --> 00:05:17,160
He's being this polite.

120
00:05:17,160 --> 00:05:18,920
How on earth is he rude, All-New?

121
00:05:18,920 --> 00:05:20,680
But he wasn't acting like this
when I ran into him!

122
00:05:20,680 --> 00:05:22,840
Hey, man.
Speak like your normal self.

123
00:05:22,840 --> 00:05:23,680
Yes, sir.

124
00:05:23,680 --> 00:05:24,640
No.

125
00:05:24,640 --> 00:05:26,160
Rule number 28...

126
00:05:26,160 --> 00:05:28,720
Anyone who slanders...

127
00:05:28,720 --> 00:05:31,360
or acts poorly towards the AFS...

128
00:05:31,360 --> 00:05:33,960
will be dismissed from First Class.

129
00:05:37,280 --> 00:05:40,360
Welcome to our department, sir.

130
00:05:40,360 --> 00:05:41,720
That's wonderful then.

131
00:05:41,720 --> 00:05:43,320
Therefore, All-New...

132
00:05:43,320 --> 00:05:44,800
you must act as the host for Mr. Prayoon...

133
00:05:44,800 --> 00:05:46,080
throughout this entire project.

134
00:05:46,080 --> 00:05:47,520
With pleasure.

135
00:05:47,520 --> 00:05:48,840
What?!

136
00:05:51,040 --> 00:05:52,320
I'm so glad.

137
00:05:52,320 --> 00:05:55,080
Everyone is getting along so well.

138
00:05:55,320 --> 00:05:58,840
Just wonderful.

139
00:06:05,760 --> 00:06:06,560
Hey, Tid-Gift!

140
00:06:07,200 --> 00:06:08,040
Take it back!

141
00:06:08,480 --> 00:06:09,120
What the hell?

142
00:06:09,120 --> 00:06:10,240
Just take your damn things back!

143
00:06:10,240 --> 00:06:12,640
Hey! My raggy pillow!

144
00:06:13,280 --> 00:06:15,040
My free promo water bottle!

145
00:06:17,080 --> 00:06:18,160
My favorite shirt!

146
00:06:18,160 --> 00:06:19,400
Wait, you actually wore this?

147
00:06:20,120 --> 00:06:21,960
Shit, how did you even fit into it?

148
00:06:22,960 --> 00:06:24,880
How I wore it is
none of your damn business!

149
00:06:24,880 --> 00:06:25,720
Hold on a second.

150
00:06:25,720 --> 00:06:26,920
When the hell
did you even take these?

151
00:06:26,920 --> 00:06:27,960
I don't remember this at all.

152
00:06:27,960 --> 00:06:29,440
Well, now you do.

153
00:06:29,440 --> 00:06:31,320
I've returned all your stuff.

154
00:06:31,960 --> 00:06:33,440
So anything that belongs to me...

155
00:06:33,440 --> 00:06:35,400
you have no right to mess with.

156
00:06:36,800 --> 00:06:37,480
What the hell
are you talking about?

157
00:06:37,480 --> 00:06:38,680
About my ex!

158
00:06:40,200 --> 00:06:41,840
Even if he's my ex...

159
00:06:41,840 --> 00:06:43,520
you still have no right
to mess with him!

160
00:06:43,920 --> 00:06:44,760
Do you understand?

161
00:06:44,760 --> 00:06:46,240
You just love messing
with other people's stuff.

162
00:06:50,120 --> 00:06:51,440
Is he on his period
or something?

163
00:06:51,440 --> 00:06:52,800
What is wrong with him?

164
00:06:52,800 --> 00:06:55,160
Can I still wear this?
Let me test it.

165
00:07:00,120 --> 00:07:01,360
Ugh, this smells!

166
00:07:05,880 --> 00:07:08,160
Not only am I
an outstanding employee...

167
00:07:08,160 --> 00:07:10,800
of Glamorous Airline...

168
00:07:10,800 --> 00:07:12,800
and the most
beautiful flight attendant...

169
00:07:12,800 --> 00:07:14,960
at this airline...

170
00:07:14,960 --> 00:07:16,720
but when it comes
to company business...

171
00:07:16,720 --> 00:07:19,400
I know every single
nook and cranny.

172
00:07:19,400 --> 00:07:20,480
Therefore, today...

173
00:07:20,480 --> 00:07:21,640
I will personally give
Technician Yoon...

174
00:07:21,640 --> 00:07:24,760
a tour of every nook and cranny
of our company!

175
00:07:24,760 --> 00:07:26,040
Thank you very much, ma'am.

176
00:07:26,040 --> 00:07:28,360
Oh, goodness!

177
00:07:28,360 --> 00:07:30,600
You are such a
polite and humble person.

178
00:07:30,600 --> 00:07:32,800
Totally my type...

179
00:07:33,600 --> 00:07:35,160
Let's start with the first area.

180
00:07:35,160 --> 00:07:38,000
Over on this side is the sofa...

181
00:07:38,000 --> 00:07:40,240
and that's a table,
and that's a book.

182
00:07:40,240 --> 00:07:41,200
Sky...no.

183
00:07:41,200 --> 00:07:41,920
No, what?

184
00:07:41,920 --> 00:07:43,160
Are these in a rice cooker
or something?

185
00:07:43,160 --> 00:07:44,440
They wanted you to introduce

186
00:07:44,440 --> 00:07:46,400
the technical work
in our department.

187
00:07:46,400 --> 00:07:47,360
Oh, really?

188
00:07:49,400 --> 00:07:52,280
Alright then!
And these are the technical tools...

189
00:07:52,280 --> 00:07:54,280
that you need to know.

190
00:07:54,280 --> 00:07:56,560
I will introduce them to you.

191
00:07:56,560 --> 00:07:58,120
Let's start with the first item.

192
00:07:58,680 --> 00:08:00,920
As for this one, it is...

193
00:08:02,560 --> 00:08:03,240
It's...

194
00:08:03,240 --> 00:08:04,360
It's a wrench, ma'am.

195
00:08:05,120 --> 00:08:07,920
That's correct!
This is indeed a wrench.

196
00:08:07,920 --> 00:08:10,360
But there are
so many pieces of equipment.

197
00:08:10,360 --> 00:08:12,880
How about this?
I will...

198
00:08:12,880 --> 00:08:15,000
write them down for you.

199
00:08:15,000 --> 00:08:16,080
Thank you, ma'am.

200
00:08:16,080 --> 00:08:17,400
It'll be easier to remember, right?

201
00:08:17,400 --> 00:08:21,760
First item, a wrench...
a wrench...

202
00:08:22,120 --> 00:08:23,920
Oh!

203
00:08:23,920 --> 00:08:25,560
Huh?

204
00:08:25,560 --> 00:08:26,560
The lead broke.

205
00:08:31,200 --> 00:08:33,520
Should I fix it for you, ma'am?

206
00:08:33,520 --> 00:08:35,600
It's alright.
The lead might just be a bit jammed.

207
00:08:35,600 --> 00:08:36,880
It should come out if I click it.

208
00:08:38,040 --> 00:08:41,080
If you do that, it will...

209
00:08:41,080 --> 00:08:42,640
It's fine.
It's simple.

210
00:08:42,640 --> 00:08:44,640
I can handle it.

211
00:08:55,360 --> 00:08:57,560
I think it's probably broken.

212
00:08:57,560 --> 00:08:59,240
I will go get a new one then.

213
00:08:59,240 --> 00:09:01,240
Just a moment.
Wait here, okay?

214
00:09:06,200 --> 00:09:07,760
Let me try...

215
00:09:07,760 --> 00:09:10,840
and see if it can be fixed.

216
00:09:11,400 --> 00:09:13,640
You just have to click it.
Click it harder.

217
00:09:13,640 --> 00:09:15,120
The more jammed it gets,
the more you click. Click!

218
00:09:27,240 --> 00:09:29,040
I can't take this shit anymore!

219
00:09:29,040 --> 00:09:30,200
If something is broken,
it needs to be fixed!

220
00:09:30,200 --> 00:09:31,200
Why the hell are you
clicking it so much, Glasses?

221
00:09:31,200 --> 00:09:32,200
Are you out of your mind?
You idiot!

222
00:09:32,560 --> 00:09:33,160
You dumbass!

223
00:09:33,160 --> 00:09:36,040
You've finally shown
your true colors!

224
00:09:36,040 --> 00:09:37,240
Sky...

225
00:09:37,240 --> 00:09:38,920
Shut the hell up!
Shut up!

226
00:09:39,600 --> 00:09:42,360
Yeah, I'm in therapy
for anger management!

227
00:09:42,360 --> 00:09:44,560
So don't push your luck, Glasses!

228
00:09:46,160 --> 00:09:49,480
Oh, so you're trying to
change yourself? Sorry about that.

229
00:09:51,840 --> 00:09:53,280
It's quite alright, sir.

230
00:09:54,040 --> 00:09:54,880
This is getting weird.

231
00:09:54,880 --> 00:09:57,280
So don't get on my nerves, sir.

232
00:09:58,520 --> 00:09:59,680
These aren't yours, right?

233
00:09:59,680 --> 00:10:01,240
I see you brought your own tools.

234
00:10:01,240 --> 00:10:03,760
Oh, those aren't technical tools, sir.

235
00:10:03,760 --> 00:10:05,280
Not technical tools?

236
00:10:05,720 --> 00:10:06,760
Then what are they?

237
00:10:06,760 --> 00:10:08,800
They're just everyday items, sir.

238
00:10:08,800 --> 00:10:10,520
Everyday items?
Then let me take a look.

239
00:10:13,520 --> 00:10:15,520
Uh, Sky, let me help
you find a pencil, ma'am.

240
00:10:19,720 --> 00:10:20,560
This is getting weird.

241
00:10:20,560 --> 00:10:21,560
Sir and ma'am?

242
00:10:26,760 --> 00:10:29,560
Kree, listen to me.

243
00:10:29,560 --> 00:10:30,840
Today's theme is so simple.

244
00:10:30,840 --> 00:10:32,640
Spicy eating show,
just eat in a way...

245
00:10:32,640 --> 00:10:34,640
that makes people want to buy it.

246
00:10:34,640 --> 00:10:36,120
Look at our product.

247
00:10:36,120 --> 00:10:37,360
Even though
it looks like dog food,

248
00:10:37,360 --> 00:10:38,640
it's actually human food.

249
00:10:38,640 --> 00:10:40,800
You have only one job,

250
00:10:40,800 --> 00:10:43,400
just sit there and shut up.

251
00:10:43,400 --> 00:10:45,040
You're good-looking.

252
00:10:45,040 --> 00:10:46,640
People like looking at your face.

253
00:10:46,640 --> 00:10:47,480
Alright.

254
00:10:47,480 --> 00:10:49,480
I just told you to shut up!

255
00:10:49,480 --> 00:10:50,920
Because the moment
you open your mouth...

256
00:10:50,920 --> 00:10:51,880
it's a total flop.

257
00:10:51,880 --> 00:10:52,800
The views will drop.

258
00:10:52,800 --> 00:10:53,920
Got it?

259
00:10:53,920 --> 00:10:56,800
If you're ready, press start.

260
00:10:56,800 --> 00:11:00,800
Hi everyone!
Oh, look who's here...

261
00:11:00,880 --> 00:11:04,320
Our guest, Kreetha!

262
00:11:04,320 --> 00:11:07,000
Kreetha is half-Russian.

263
00:11:07,000 --> 00:11:11,000
He can't speak Thai at all,
and he can't read it either.

264
00:11:11,720 --> 00:11:14,000
I really want to
hear Kreetha's voice.

265
00:11:14,000 --> 00:11:16,320
He's not really big on talking.

266
00:11:16,320 --> 00:11:19,040
I want to know
what his voice sounds like.

267
00:11:19,040 --> 00:11:20,280
Uh...

268
00:11:20,280 --> 00:11:24,080
How about just one word then?
Just one word, okay?

269
00:11:25,480 --> 00:11:27,880
He's a bit shy,
give him a second.

270
00:11:27,880 --> 00:11:29,880
One word.

271
00:11:32,560 --> 00:11:33,560
One word.

272
00:11:36,000 --> 00:11:37,880
It feels like you're forcing him.

273
00:11:37,880 --> 00:11:39,920
No one is forcing him!

274
00:11:39,920 --> 00:11:40,920
One word.

275
00:11:46,280 --> 00:11:47,280
One word.

276
00:11:47,760 --> 00:11:48,760
Say it.

277
00:11:53,800 --> 00:11:56,040
Oh, Chaba!

278
00:11:56,040 --> 00:11:58,480
Are you going to
let me speak or not? Seriously!

279
00:11:58,480 --> 00:12:00,280
You're practically
strangling me to death here.

280
00:12:00,280 --> 00:12:01,680
There, I spoke. Happy?

281
00:12:01,680 --> 00:12:03,480
Oh, Kree completely loses
his charm when he speaks.

282
00:12:03,480 --> 00:12:04,640
Unfollowing now.

283
00:12:04,640 --> 00:12:06,480
Can't accept this behavior.

284
00:12:06,480 --> 00:12:08,200
Stop it!
Turn it off!

285
00:12:09,560 --> 00:12:11,120
You just made a whole speech!

286
00:12:11,120 --> 00:12:12,440
You were strangling me like that!

287
00:12:12,440 --> 00:12:13,800
I said one word, ONE WORD!

288
00:12:13,800 --> 00:12:14,840
You should've just said, "Yes."

289
00:12:14,840 --> 00:12:16,600
Hi.

290
00:12:16,600 --> 00:12:18,000
Hello.

291
00:12:18,000 --> 00:12:18,840
No?

292
00:12:18,840 --> 00:12:19,840
No!

293
00:12:20,880 --> 00:12:23,680
God dammit, Kreetha!

294
00:12:38,480 --> 00:12:40,440
I knew it!

295
00:12:40,440 --> 00:12:42,400
You must be one of them!

296
00:12:42,400 --> 00:12:44,200
One of who, Mr. All-New?

297
00:12:44,200 --> 00:12:46,200
Oh! Mr. All-New,
a bomb! A bomb!

298
00:12:46,440 --> 00:12:47,320
What should we do?

299
00:12:47,320 --> 00:12:48,160
Hey, stop faking it!

300
00:12:48,160 --> 00:12:49,520
Should I call the police?

301
00:12:49,520 --> 00:12:51,280
Let me call them for you.

302
00:12:51,280 --> 00:12:52,280
Hey, stop acting!

303
00:12:52,280 --> 00:12:53,680
Mr. All-New,
what should we do?

304
00:12:53,680 --> 00:12:54,920
Should I...
should I send an email?

305
00:12:54,920 --> 00:12:56,320
Mr. All-New,
do you know anyone?

306
00:12:56,320 --> 00:12:57,440
Drop the act already.

307
00:12:58,800 --> 00:13:01,320
Fine, I'll drop the act.

308
00:13:02,680 --> 00:13:04,120
I'm getting sick of myself too.

309
00:13:17,280 --> 00:13:18,360
Why are you putting your hands up?

310
00:13:18,360 --> 00:13:21,080
Well, I'm surrendering!

311
00:13:21,080 --> 00:13:22,480
What if you shoot me?

312
00:13:22,480 --> 00:13:24,240
Shoot you with what?
I don't have a gun.

313
00:13:24,240 --> 00:13:26,120
I just came here
to catch you in the act.

314
00:13:27,160 --> 00:13:27,640
Oh.

315
00:13:27,640 --> 00:13:28,720
Well, I have one.

316
00:13:28,720 --> 00:13:30,360
Whoa! Hey!

317
00:13:30,360 --> 00:13:32,200
Whoa, calm down!

318
00:13:32,200 --> 00:13:32,680
I give up!

319
00:13:32,680 --> 00:13:33,560
Hey!

320
00:13:33,560 --> 00:13:34,200
Hey! Hey!

321
00:13:34,200 --> 00:13:35,680
What the hell
are you guys playing?

322
00:13:35,680 --> 00:13:38,040
I'm trying to sleep here,
dumbasses!

323
00:13:38,040 --> 00:13:39,960
Sky, over here!

324
00:13:39,960 --> 00:13:41,360
Sky, get out of the way!

325
00:13:41,360 --> 00:13:43,400
He told you
to get out of the way!

326
00:13:43,400 --> 00:13:44,400
Is it Chinese New Year already?

327
00:13:44,400 --> 00:13:45,800
Who the hell is
lighting firecrackers?

328
00:13:47,120 --> 00:13:47,840
Sky!

329
00:13:48,320 --> 00:13:49,240
Hey!

330
00:13:50,800 --> 00:13:51,800
Sky!

331
00:13:57,680 --> 00:13:58,760
I'm out of ammo.

332
00:13:58,760 --> 00:14:00,040
You idiot, come here.

333
00:14:00,520 --> 00:14:03,840
Press right here to eject it,
and then change it like this.

334
00:14:03,840 --> 00:14:04,760
See?
Simple as that.

335
00:14:04,760 --> 00:14:05,200
Thank you.

336
00:14:05,200 --> 00:14:06,200
You're welcome, dear.

337
00:14:08,080 --> 00:14:09,200
Sky...

338
00:14:09,200 --> 00:14:10,680
No need to mourn...

339
00:14:10,680 --> 00:14:12,680
because you'll be next.

340
00:14:16,040 --> 00:14:16,840
Don't shoot me!

341
00:14:16,840 --> 00:14:18,080
Holy shit!

342
00:14:19,600 --> 00:14:20,760
Wait, was I dreaming?

343
00:14:20,760 --> 00:14:22,160
What?

344
00:14:22,160 --> 00:14:24,080
Hey, I'm sorry, okay?

345
00:14:24,080 --> 00:14:25,840
Sorry, sorry, sorry!

346
00:14:25,840 --> 00:14:27,840
Hey, don't come near me!
I said I'm sorry!

347
00:14:27,840 --> 00:14:28,640
Hey, Glasses!

348
00:14:28,640 --> 00:14:29,480
What? What? What?

349
00:14:29,480 --> 00:14:31,720
It's okay, it's okay.

350
00:14:31,720 --> 00:14:32,840
What is it?

351
00:14:32,840 --> 00:14:35,120
I forgive you, okay?
Calm down.

352
00:14:35,120 --> 00:14:35,880
Forgive me for what?

353
00:14:35,880 --> 00:14:38,000
I don't know.
What were you apologizing for then?

354
00:14:38,000 --> 00:14:39,840
You killed Sky!

355
00:14:39,840 --> 00:14:41,120
Killed?

356
00:14:41,120 --> 00:14:41,960
Who killed who?

357
00:14:41,960 --> 00:14:43,120
Just now!

358
00:14:43,120 --> 00:14:44,360
Just now in your dream,
you mean?

359
00:14:45,560 --> 00:14:46,040
Yeah.

360
00:14:46,240 --> 00:14:46,960
Yeah.

361
00:14:46,960 --> 00:14:48,200
You evil bastard.

362
00:14:48,200 --> 00:14:48,880
You hellbound piece of shit.

363
00:14:48,880 --> 00:14:50,440
Dog-face.

364
00:14:50,440 --> 00:14:52,120
Husky-face.

365
00:14:52,120 --> 00:14:53,600
Cart Titan!

366
00:14:53,600 --> 00:14:55,040
Baboon!

367
00:14:56,080 --> 00:14:57,320
How could you do that?

368
00:14:57,960 --> 00:15:00,440
Basically, you've got
a whole zoo on your face.

369
00:15:02,840 --> 00:15:04,360
Shit, the whole safari is right here.

370
00:15:04,360 --> 00:15:05,600
Is this Safari World Airlines
or what?

371
00:15:05,760 --> 00:15:07,760
Damn, it was a dream
and it's my fault?

372
00:15:11,360 --> 00:15:14,040
Gift, please take Kree away with you.

373
00:15:14,040 --> 00:15:15,240
I can't deal with him anymore.

374
00:15:15,240 --> 00:15:15,840
Even when he just sits
there doing nothing,

375
00:15:15,840 --> 00:15:17,040
it's a complete flop.

376
00:15:18,360 --> 00:15:19,840
What do you expect me
to hire him for?

377
00:15:19,840 --> 00:15:21,280
I can do anything!

378
00:15:21,280 --> 00:15:24,680
Can you help make Chai
stop being so damn crazy?

379
00:15:25,920 --> 00:15:27,400
Come again?

380
00:15:28,720 --> 00:15:29,760
Never mind.

381
00:15:31,520 --> 00:15:33,240
You two can head back first.

382
00:15:33,240 --> 00:15:33,960
Before Chai...

383
00:15:33,960 --> 00:15:35,360
Before I do what?

384
00:15:36,160 --> 00:15:36,880
Before I find out what else...

385
00:15:36,880 --> 00:15:38,680
you're trying to steal from me, right?

386
00:15:39,560 --> 00:15:42,040
Even when I'm on my period,

387
00:15:42,040 --> 00:15:43,600
I'm still not as whiny as you!

388
00:15:43,600 --> 00:15:44,360
What's going on here?

389
00:15:44,360 --> 00:15:45,960
Have you ever had a friend
secretly sleep with your ex?

390
00:15:46,120 --> 00:15:49,120
Then next time, you should put
a warning label on them...

391
00:15:49,120 --> 00:15:50,560
showing exactly who your exes are.

392
00:15:50,560 --> 00:15:51,360
And why the hell did you
pretend to be a fake gay guy...

393
00:15:51,360 --> 00:15:52,600
just to invade my market?

394
00:15:52,880 --> 00:15:55,320
Your "market" is literally the whole world!

395
00:15:55,640 --> 00:15:57,920
But out of all people, you just had
to end up pulling my ex?

396
00:15:58,600 --> 00:16:00,160
I didn't know!

397
00:16:00,160 --> 00:16:01,880
What on earth is happening here?

398
00:16:01,880 --> 00:16:03,560
You dumbass! Idiot!

399
00:16:03,960 --> 00:16:05,920
They've explained it so clearly.

400
00:16:05,920 --> 00:16:07,040
Do they need to act out...

401
00:16:07,040 --> 00:16:08,800
a whole moral drama
right in front of your face?

402
00:16:09,560 --> 00:16:11,480
Keep a close eye
on your friend, Chaba.

403
00:16:11,480 --> 00:16:13,120
Watch out or she might
secretly sleep with your ex.

404
00:16:13,960 --> 00:16:14,880
I don't think so.

405
00:16:15,920 --> 00:16:16,480
How would you know?

406
00:16:16,600 --> 00:16:17,800
Well, I've never had an ex,

407
00:16:17,800 --> 00:16:18,920
so who is she going to sleep with?

408
00:16:19,840 --> 00:16:22,360
If I had known, I wouldn't have
messed with him, okay?

409
00:16:22,360 --> 00:16:24,880
Gift, did you secretly
hook up with Suea-Khrong,

410
00:16:24,880 --> 00:16:25,920
Chai's ex?

411
00:16:25,920 --> 00:16:27,000
No.

412
00:16:27,000 --> 00:16:27,720
Toto?

413
00:16:27,720 --> 00:16:28,320
No.

414
00:16:28,320 --> 00:16:29,080
Nana?

415
00:16:29,080 --> 00:16:29,840
No.

416
00:16:29,840 --> 00:16:30,440
Saira?

417
00:16:30,440 --> 00:16:31,280
No.

418
00:16:31,280 --> 00:16:31,920
Baki?

419
00:16:31,920 --> 00:16:32,840
No.

420
00:16:32,840 --> 00:16:33,480
Boom-Boom?

421
00:16:33,480 --> 00:16:34,120
No.

422
00:16:34,120 --> 00:16:34,680
Aom-Aom?

423
00:16:34,680 --> 00:16:35,600
No.

424
00:16:35,600 --> 00:16:36,200
Cher-Beam?

425
00:16:36,200 --> 00:16:37,040
Not that one.

426
00:16:37,040 --> 00:16:39,040
Chai has way too many exes.
I can't keep track.

427
00:16:40,480 --> 00:16:41,720
Ninja.

428
00:16:42,360 --> 00:16:43,520
His name is Ninja.

429
00:16:43,520 --> 00:16:44,800
And what about him?

430
00:16:45,120 --> 00:16:46,040
You two are acting like...

431
00:16:46,040 --> 00:16:47,600
you've never shared
the same guy before.

432
00:16:47,800 --> 00:16:51,360
But this guy has
always been in my heart.

433
00:16:54,120 --> 00:16:55,640
We first met right...

434
00:16:56,960 --> 00:16:58,680
after I graduated.

435
00:17:00,240 --> 00:17:02,080
He was my first...

436
00:17:03,600 --> 00:17:05,160
Are you faking it?

437
00:17:05,160 --> 00:17:07,120
You didn't lose your
virginity until you graduated?

438
00:17:08,200 --> 00:17:11,320
He was the first person
whose mind I couldn't read.

439
00:17:12,840 --> 00:17:16,360
And things between us had to end...

440
00:17:17,160 --> 00:17:20,120
even though both of us...

441
00:17:21,600 --> 00:17:22,360
didn't reach it yet...

442
00:17:22,360 --> 00:17:24,040
Mhm.

443
00:17:24,440 --> 00:17:26,160
What do you mean "mhm"?

444
00:17:26,160 --> 00:17:28,400
I mean things between us
were left unfinished.

445
00:17:28,400 --> 00:17:30,360
Like, it wasn't completely finalized.

446
00:17:30,360 --> 00:17:31,760
How about using the word "settled"?

447
00:17:31,760 --> 00:17:35,160
Yeah, that. Things between us
weren't settled yet.

448
00:17:35,840 --> 00:17:37,480
And then...

449
00:17:37,480 --> 00:17:39,240
he said he wanted to go abroad,

450
00:17:40,520 --> 00:17:42,040
and then he just vanished.

451
00:17:44,720 --> 00:17:46,480
Vanished just like his name.

452
00:17:48,080 --> 00:17:49,000
Ninja.

453
00:17:49,000 --> 00:17:52,720
So you two are fighting over a guy...

454
00:17:52,720 --> 00:17:56,680
whom you will never
get back together with...

455
00:17:57,960 --> 00:18:00,920
and whom you
will never see again?

456
00:18:02,160 --> 00:18:04,160
Yet you two are best friends...

457
00:18:04,160 --> 00:18:05,760
living in the same house...

458
00:18:05,760 --> 00:18:07,960
and you're seriously turning on
each other over this?

459
00:18:17,400 --> 00:18:19,200
Chai...

460
00:18:21,320 --> 00:18:23,080
I'm sorry.

461
00:18:24,880 --> 00:18:27,560
If I knew he was someone
you cared about this much,

462
00:18:27,560 --> 00:18:29,000
I wouldn't have messed with
him from the start.

463
00:18:34,560 --> 00:18:36,800
It's not just because
I care about Ninja.

464
00:18:36,800 --> 00:18:39,480
Oh?
Then what is it?

465
00:18:39,480 --> 00:18:42,160
I just didn't know how to act.

466
00:18:42,160 --> 00:18:45,520
When the two people
I care about the most...

467
00:18:46,840 --> 00:18:48,880
end up sleeping together.

468
00:18:50,840 --> 00:18:53,720
You're someone I care about
a lot too, Tid-Gift.

469
00:18:56,120 --> 00:18:57,720
Care?

470
00:18:57,720 --> 00:18:58,880
In what way?

471
00:18:58,880 --> 00:19:00,560
Like, more than a friend?

472
00:19:04,120 --> 00:19:05,320
Yeah.

473
00:19:07,760 --> 00:19:09,360
More than a friend.

474
00:19:09,360 --> 00:19:10,680
I mean, it's definitely
more than just a friend.

475
00:19:14,880 --> 00:19:17,520
We're housemates.

476
00:19:17,520 --> 00:19:20,280
I see her face more often
than I see my own dad's.

477
00:19:20,280 --> 00:19:23,960
Ah.

478
00:19:23,960 --> 00:19:25,640
Right, I get it now.

479
00:19:25,640 --> 00:19:28,160
Now that you've opened up
to each other...

480
00:19:28,160 --> 00:19:29,960
there's no need to
fight over someone...

481
00:19:29,960 --> 00:19:31,720
whom you're never going
to see ever again, right?

482
00:19:38,160 --> 00:19:39,440
Ninja just texted me.

483
00:19:47,720 --> 00:19:49,680
Technician Yoon really
is suspicious, Sky.

484
00:19:49,680 --> 00:19:51,680
I've seen a box just like that
at Pong's safe house.

485
00:19:51,680 --> 00:19:53,000
You mean that box?

486
00:19:56,200 --> 00:19:59,880
Oh, boxes like that
are everywhere.

487
00:20:00,640 --> 00:20:02,280
And a good guy like
Technician Yoon...

488
00:20:02,560 --> 00:20:04,440
how could he possibly
hurt anyone?

489
00:20:06,480 --> 00:20:07,480
Where are you running off to?

490
00:20:19,080 --> 00:20:21,120
Uh, police!
Police, help!

491
00:20:21,120 --> 00:20:22,040
Somebody, help!

492
00:20:22,040 --> 00:20:23,080
Cut!

493
00:20:24,200 --> 00:20:26,840
Hey, kid, take it easy!
We're filming a movie here.

494
00:20:28,200 --> 00:20:29,160
Filming a movie?

495
00:20:29,160 --> 00:20:30,400
Uh, he's my friend.

496
00:20:30,400 --> 00:20:32,040
I'll handle this, sir.

497
00:20:32,040 --> 00:20:34,200
Your part is done.
You can go.

498
00:20:34,200 --> 00:20:35,240
Thank you, sir.

499
00:20:40,080 --> 00:20:43,280
Wait...so they were filming a movie?

500
00:20:43,280 --> 00:20:44,960
You're an actor?

501
00:20:44,960 --> 00:20:46,160
You're a performer?

502
00:20:46,680 --> 00:20:48,560
What's going on?
I'm so confused.

503
00:20:48,560 --> 00:20:51,360
I have a side job
as a stuntman, ma'am.

504
00:20:51,360 --> 00:20:55,640
Oh!
And what movie are you filming?

505
00:20:56,120 --> 00:20:57,680
The Drip is Here, ma'am.

506
00:20:58,920 --> 00:21:01,080
The Drip is Here?
What kind of movie is that?

507
00:21:01,360 --> 00:21:04,000
I play a plumber, ma'am.

508
00:21:04,000 --> 00:21:05,520
I fix pipes and stuff.

509
00:21:05,520 --> 00:21:07,680
Whenever there's a drip,
I go to fix it.

510
00:21:07,680 --> 00:21:09,400
Since the drip is
right here, ma'am...

511
00:21:09,400 --> 00:21:11,400
I had to come and fix it, ma'am.

512
00:21:13,200 --> 00:21:15,840
See?
All-New, I told you.

513
00:21:15,840 --> 00:21:18,040
Technician Yoon isn't
a bad person at all.

514
00:21:18,640 --> 00:21:19,480
But it's still weird.

515
00:21:19,480 --> 00:21:22,360
Who carries around
a heavy black box like that?

516
00:21:22,640 --> 00:21:24,480
Should we just open it and see?

517
00:21:24,480 --> 00:21:25,800
I need these items, sir.

518
00:21:25,800 --> 00:21:26,720
Oh, you need them?

519
00:21:26,920 --> 00:21:27,800
Yes, sir. So...

520
00:21:27,840 --> 00:21:28,680
if you'll excuse me...

521
00:21:28,680 --> 00:21:29,680
Let's see it.

522
00:21:32,400 --> 00:21:35,280
I knew it! It has to be...

523
00:21:36,240 --> 00:21:37,640
cosmetics?

524
00:21:38,760 --> 00:21:41,200
Hey, did you swap your box
with the makeup artist?

525
00:21:42,160 --> 00:21:43,160
Prayoon's...

526
00:21:47,120 --> 00:21:48,120
Prayoon's...

527
00:21:50,200 --> 00:21:51,200
Prayoon's...

528
00:21:51,200 --> 00:21:54,160
I have sensitive skin, ma'am.

529
00:21:54,160 --> 00:21:57,000
So I have to use my own
personal products when I'm on set.

530
00:22:00,560 --> 00:22:01,440
Hey, kid!

531
00:22:01,840 --> 00:22:03,840
Someone named Peck
is here asking for you.

532
00:22:05,880 --> 00:22:07,520
Thank you, sir.

533
00:22:07,520 --> 00:22:08,720
If you'll excuse me...

534
00:22:12,040 --> 00:22:13,040
Did you hear that?

535
00:22:13,040 --> 00:22:14,000
I heard it.

536
00:22:14,480 --> 00:22:15,600
He said...

537
00:22:16,320 --> 00:22:17,360
Yes, sir.

538
00:22:17,360 --> 00:22:18,280
Yes, ma'am.

539
00:22:18,280 --> 00:22:20,440
Why is it so hard
to be such a polite person?

540
00:22:20,440 --> 00:22:22,600
No, he said he knows
someone named Peck.

541
00:22:22,600 --> 00:22:23,480
I know her too.

542
00:22:23,480 --> 00:22:24,360
Which Peck?

543
00:22:24,360 --> 00:22:25,320
You know, Peck!

544
00:22:25,320 --> 00:22:26,280
The one whose mom is named Piak...

545
00:22:26,280 --> 00:22:27,240
dad is named Pao...

546
00:22:27,240 --> 00:22:28,840
and whose younger
sibling is named Pood.

547
00:22:28,840 --> 00:22:30,840
I meant Peck-Pong.

548
00:22:42,960 --> 00:22:44,160
There's an anesthetic
inside this envelope.

549
00:22:44,160 --> 00:22:45,840
If anyone opens it,
the drug will disperse...

